text.data-name: Doctor, I am feeling chest pain since yesterday. The pain is continuous and is located just in the middle of my chest, worsening when I breathe and when I lay down on my bed. I suffer from arterial hypertension and smoke 20 cigarettes every day. My father
text.tspan: Doctor, I am feeling chest pain since yesterday. The pain is continuous and is located
just in the middle of my chest, worsening when I breathe and when I lay down on my
bed. I suffer from arterial hypertension and smoke 20 cigarettes every day. My father
had a “heart attack” at my age and I am very worried about it.

text.data-name: PHYSICAL EXAMINATION Cardiac and pulmonary auscultation are normal; chest pain does not worse with palpation of the thorax; there is no jugular stasis nor lower limb edema.
